# .env is OPTIONAL. Every variable below has a sensible default baked into
# compose.yml via ${VAR:-default} substitution, so `make run` works out of
# the box without a .env file. Copy this file to .env only if you want to
# override one or more values.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Docker Compose automatically reads .env from the project root for
# variable substitution, so any uncommented line here (once copied to .env)
# will override the default in compose.yml.

# ─── PostgreSQL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Consumed by the postgres image entrypoint on first init.
# POSTGRES_USER=dhis
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=dhis
# POSTGRES_DB=dhis
# TZ=Europe/Oslo

# ─── pgAdmin ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The pgadmin4 image requires these to set up its internal config DB.
# Desktop mode is set in compose.pgadmin.yml so these become the master
# identity values inside pgAdmin and are otherwise invisible.
# PGADMIN_DEFAULT_EMAIL=admin@admin.com
# PGADMIN_DEFAULT_PASSWORD=root

# ─── DHIS2 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# initdb.sh defaults DHIS2_USER to 'admin' and DHIS2_PASSWORD to 'district'.
# The password is bcrypt-hashed at init time and applied to every row in
# the userinfo table, so every existing DHIS2 user ends up with this
# password. Change DHIS2_PASSWORD and re-run `make run` to re-seed.
# DHIS2_USER=admin
# DHIS2_PASSWORD=district
